 if the test resources for reflect-config avoid broad JDK methods. Hmm, it seems a bit broad, right? So maybe I should specify the queried methods instead. But wait, the schema in the legacy reflect-config supports \\\"methods\\\" and not \\\"queriedMethods,\\\" which is a little confusing! I wonder how I can streamline this to avoid potential issues while still following the required configurations. Let’s dig deeper into those specifications!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering method inclusion**\\n\\nI’m realizing that if `allPublicMethods` doesn’t include inherited methods and the field is null, the test will fail. I could add `java.sql.ResultSet` to `allPublicMethods`, but I might still need to check the metadata for `OracleResultSet` when using `Class.getMethod`. Hmm, would it be better to add both? Since this is just for test resources, I think it makes sense to do it. Let's move forward with that!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_o7Zjs5YP6sOPAUr0AuhGsUuf|fc_09592ec50b5286830169f82e07bfd48195973fddf76ecd5552", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/com_oracle_database_jdbc/ojdbc11/reflect-config.json", "edits": [{"oldText": "  {\n    \"name\": \"oracle.jdbc.internal.OracleResultSet\",\n    \"allPublicMethods\": true\n  }\n]", "newText": "  {\n    \"name\": \"oracle.jdbc.internal.OracleResultSet\",\n    \"allPublicMethods\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"java.sql.ResultSet\",\n    \"allPublicMethods\": true\n  }\n]"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 855, "output": 1001, "cacheRead": 59904, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 61760, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777872377166, "responseId": "resp_09592ec50b5286830169f82df9d0bc8195955b9a2da7961c9e"}}
